If you know me at all, you know I am NOT a morning person but I had TOTALLY lost my routine when I started my new 9-5 job. I would normally exercise in the evenings but I was just too lazy after work and there were other things to do. Sooo, finally I got my big butt out of bed at 6:30 this morning. This is a huge deal for me. Haha! Hopefully I can make this my new normal. I left Seattle yesterday morning and headed up to Vancouver Island where I met up with @vagabondhearts. Our first hike on the island was to this waterfall, Ammonite Falls. 
We'll be spending the next few days exploring around Tofino so be prepared for lots of green forests and rugged coastlines. 🌊🌿
